This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the use of neural networks and their performance in various machine learning tasks. It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it specifically focuses on neural networks. Additionally, the paper mentions language modeling, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of sparseness to reduce memory and computation footprint could also place this paper in the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the mention of matrix-vector multiplication could suggest that this paper could also belong to the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision), as this operation is commonly used in image processing.
